queryForeignTokenID(address).details: Get token id of an ERC20 contract address.

quoteRegisterTokenFee().details: Quote a fee in Ether for registering a token, covering 1. Delivery costs to BridgeHub 2. XCM Execution costs on AssetHub

quoteSendTokenFee(address,uint32,uint128.details: Quote a fee in Ether for sending a token 1. Delivery costs to BridgeHub 2. XCM execution costs on destinationChain

registerToken(address).details: Register an ERC20 token and create a wrapped derivative on AssetHub in the `ForeignAssets` pallet.

sendToken(address,uint32,(uint8,bytes),u.details: Send a token to parachain `destinationChain` and deposit into account `destinationAddress`. The user can send native Ether by supplying `address(0)` for the `token` parameter.

submitV1((bytes32,uint64,uint8,bytes,uin.details: Submit a message from Polkadot for verification and dispatch

params.headerProof: A proof that the commitment is included in parachain header that was        finalized by BEEFY.
params.leafProof: A message proof used to verify that the message is in the merkle tree        committed by the OutboundQueue pallet.
params.message: A message produced by the OutboundQueue pallet on BridgeHub

v1_handleUpgrade(bytes).details: Perform an upgrade of the gateway

v2_createAgent(bytes32).details: Creates a new agent contract to act as a proxy for the remote location      identified by `id`

v2_isDispatched(uint64).details: Check if an inbound message was previously accepted and dispatched

v2_submit((bytes32,uint64,bytes32,(uint8.details: Submit a message from Polkadot for verification and dispatch

params.headerProof: A proof that the commitment is included in parachain header that was        finalized by BEEFY.
params.leafProof: A message proof used to verify that the message is in the merkle tree        committed by the OutboundQueue pallet
params.message: A message produced by the OutboundQueue pallet on BridgeHub
params.rewardAddress: An `AccountId` on BridgeHub that can claim rewards for relaying        this message, after the relayer has submitted a delivery receipt back to BridgeHub.

initialize(bytes).notice: Initialize storage within the `GatewayProxy` contract using this initializer. This initializer cannot be called externally via the proxy as the function selector is overshadowed in the proxy. This implementation is only intended to initialize storage for initial deployments of the `GatewayProxy` contract to transient or long-lived testnets. The `GatewayProxy` deployed to Ethereum mainnet already has its storage initialized. When its logic contract needs to upgraded, a new logic contract should be developed that inherits from this base `Gateway` contract. Particularly, the `initialize` function must be overridden to ensure selective initialization of storage fields relevant to the upgrade. ```solidity contract Gateway202508 is Gateway {     function initialize(bytes calldata data) external override {         if (ERC1967.load() == address(0)) {             revert Unauthorized();         }         # Initialization routines here...     } } ```
